  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">UN Joint Program for Strengthening Inclusive Social Cohesion and Economic Resilience in Abyei Area, Sudan</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project was developed through a series of consultations, workshops and discussions with a wide range of stakeholders at various levels in order to provide better coordinated programmatic interventions in Abyei Area (Sudan). A recent security council resolution emphasized the important nexus between peace and development, and more specifically the mutually reinforcing effect that security and political facilitation, on the one hand, and recovery and development programme could have for the stabilization of the Abyei area. The goal of this UN joint programme is improved nexus of humanitarian-recovery/development sustaining peace through increased inter-communal social cohesion and economic resilience. In doing so, the outcomes are improved social cohesion for inter-communal equitable recovery/ development between Dinka and Misseriya, and increased economic resilience for communities. The UN joint programme aims at increasing coherence within the humanitarian &#x2013; recovery, development - peacebuilding nexus in order to adequately and efficiently address protracted multi-faceted needs.</narrative>
  </description>
